conomic performance and opportunities for workers. Unusual in providing a comprehensive theoretical perspective that is grounded in detailed case research, this book points the way to a better future, not just for elite knowledge workers but for everyone.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aEmployment forecastingzUnited States. 0aLabor marketzUnited States. 0aManufacturing industriesxEmployeesxSupply and demandzUnited StatesxForecasting. 0aService industries workersxSupply and demandzUnited StatesxForecasting. 4aGeneral Economics. 4aLabor History.1 aAlic, John A., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aWial, Howard, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013z978311053615740uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150172559340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501725593423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501725593/original  a978-3-11-053615-7  Cornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles